Class Algae

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectfx.resources.Resource
com.example.projectfx.resources.Algae
All Implemented Interfaces:
Consumable
public class Algae extends Resource
Represents algae as a resource in the ecosystem. Algae have a specific reproduction rate and can be regenerated based on that rate. They can also be consumed by species.

    • isConsumed

      public boolean isConsumed()
      Determines whether the algae has been consumed. Since algae can be consumed, this method checks if the algae is still available.
      Returns:
      false because algae is not consumed fully after one action.
